    {'question': 'What is the "time value of money" principle that NPV is based on?', 'options': ['Money loses value over time due to inflation only', 'A dollar today is worth more than a dollar tomorrow because it can be invested to earn a return', 'All investments eventually become worthless', 'Future cash flows are always more valuable than present ones'], 'correctIndex': 1, 'explanation': 'The time value of money says that \$1 today is worth more than \$1 tomorrow because today\'s dollar can be invested to earn a return.'},
    {'question': 'What is the Internal Rate of Return (IRR)?', 'options': ['The total profit from an investment', 'The discount rate that makes the NPV of an investment exactly equal to zero', 'The interest rate on the company\'s bank loans', 'The inflation rate during the investment period'], 'correctIndex': 1, 'explanation': 'IRR is the discount rate where NPV = 0. It represents the project\'s actual rate of return. If IRR > WACC, the project creates value.'},
    {'question': 'What are the two components of operating decisions?', 'options': ['Revenue Management and Cost Cutting', 'Working Capital Management (money on paper) and Cash Flow Management (money on hand)', 'Debt Management and Equity Management', 'Internal Investment and External Investment'], 'correctIndex': 1, 'explanation': 'Operating decisions have two components: Working Capital Management (managing accounting entries) and Cash Flow Management (managing actual cash in the bank).'},
